#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.70"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.70:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.70:0.2"
msgid "7. Saññāvagga"
msgstr "7. Perceptions"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.70:0.3"
msgid "70. Āsavakkhayasutta"
msgstr "70. The Ending of Defilements"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.70:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these five things, when developed and cultivated, lead to the "
"ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.70:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.70:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, "
"sabbaloke anabhiratasaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī, maraṇasaññā kho "
"panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the "
"repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, "
"observes the impermanence of all conditions, and has well established the "
"perception of their own death."

msgctxt "an5.70:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā āsavānaṃ khayāya "
"saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These five things, when developed and cultivated, lead to the ending of "
"defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.70:1.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.70:1.6"
msgid "Saññāvaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.70:2.1"
msgid "Dve ca saññā dve vaḍḍhī ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.70:2.2"
msgid "sākacchena ca sājīvaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.70:2.3"
msgid "Iddhipādā ca dve vuttā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.70:2.4"
msgid "nibbidā cāsavakkhayāti."
msgstr ""
